      {
        "type": "notices",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In the Salon de Famille de Louis-Philippe of the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grand_Trianon",
                  "title": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grand Trianon"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Grand Trianon"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in Versailles a painting from "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/René-Antoine_Houasse",
                  "title": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/René-Antoine Houasse"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "René-Antoine Houasse"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", “Morpheus awakening as Iris draws near” (also “Iris and Morpheus”) can be seen."
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Based on a part of Book XI of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metamorphoses",
                  "title": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metamorphoses"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "The Metamorphoses"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " written by "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ovid",
                  "title": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ovid"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Ovid"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", it represents the particular moment when "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iris_(mythology)",
                  "title": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iris_(mythology)"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Iris"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", messager of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Juno_(mythology)",
                  "title": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Juno_(mythology)"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Juno"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " enters the cave of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypnos",
                  "title": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypnos"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "the Sleep"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to order to him to make "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcyone",
                  "title": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcyone"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Alcynoe"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " dream."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              },
              {
                "type": "spancolor",
                "attrs": {
                  "color": "rgb(61, 139, 61)"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Iris"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "sup"
              }
            ],
            "text": "583"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " but Juno could not long accept as hers"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "these supplications on behalf of one"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "then dead; and that she might persuade Halcyone"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "to turn her death-polluted hands away"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from hallowed altars, Juno said in haste,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "“O, Iris, best of all my messengers,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "go quickly to the dreadful court of Sleep,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "and in my name command him to despatch"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "a dream in the shape of Ceyx, who is dead,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "and tell Halcyone the woeful truth.”"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "So she commanded.—Iris instantly"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "assumed a garment of a thousand tints;"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "and as she marked the high skies with her arch,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "went swiftly thence as ordered, to the place"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "where Sleep was then concealed beneath a rock."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Near the Cimmerian Land there is a cave,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "with a long entrance, in a hallowed mountain,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "the home of slothful Sleep. To that dark cave"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "the Sun, when rising or in middle skies,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "or setting, never can approach with light."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "There dense fogs, mingled with the dark, exhale"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "darkness from the black soil—and all that place"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "is shadowed in a deep mysterious gloom."
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "No wakeful bird with visage crested high"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "calls forth the morning's beauty in clear notes;"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "nor do the watchful dogs, more watchful geese,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "sup"
              }
            ],
            "text": "600"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " nor wild beasts, cattle, nor the waving trees,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "make sound or whisper; and the human voice"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "is never heard there—silent Rest is there."
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "But, from the bottom of a rock beneath,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Lethean waters of a stream ooze forth,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "sounds of a rivulet, which trickle with"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "soft murmuring amid the pebbles and"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "invite soft sleep. Before the cavern doors"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "most fertile poppies and a wealth of herbs"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "bloom in abundance, from the juice of which"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "the humid night-hours gather sleep and spread"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "it over darkened Earth. No door is in"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "that cavern-home and not a hinge's noise"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "nor guarding porter's voice disturbs the calm."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "But in the middle is a resting-couch,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "raised high on night-black ebony and soft"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "with feathered cushions, all jet black, concealed"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "by a rich coverlet as dark as night,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "on which the god of sleep, dissolved in sloth"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "lies with unmoving limbs. Around him there"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "in all directions, unsubstantial dreams"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "recline in imitation of all shapes—"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "as many as the uncounted ears of corn"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "at harvest—as the myriad leaves of trees—"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "or tiny sand grains spread upon the shore."
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "As soon as Iris entered that dread gloom,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "she pushed aside the visions in her way"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "with her fair glowing hands; and instantly,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "that sacred cavern of the god of Sleep"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "was all illuminated with the glow"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "and splendor of her garment.—Out of himself"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "the god with difficulty lifted up"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "his lanquid eyes. From this small sign of life"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "relapsing many times to languid sloth,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "while nodding, with his chin he struck his breast"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "again and again. At last he roused himself"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from gloom and slumber; and, while raised upon"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "his elbow, he enquired of Iris why"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "she came to him.—He knew her by her name."
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "She answered him,"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "“O, Sleep, divine repose"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "of all things! Gentlest of the deities!"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Peace to the troubled mind, from which you drive"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "the cares of life, restorer of men's strength"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "when wearied with the toils of day, command"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "a vision that shall seem the actual form"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "of royal Ceyx to visit Trachin famed"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "for Hercules and tell Halcyone"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "his death by shipwreck. It is Juno's wish.”"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "sup"
              }
            ],
            "text": "630"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Iris departed after this was said."
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For she no longer could endure the effect"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "of slumber-vapor; and as soon as she"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "knew sleep was creeping over her tired limbs"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "she flew from there—and she departed by"
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "the rainbow, over which she came before."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "spancolor",
                "attrs": {
                  "color": "rgb(61, 139, 61)"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Ovid, “The Metamorphoses”, Book XI"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "noticesheading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Note:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "notices",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The work of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/René-Antoine_Houasse",
                  "title": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/René-Antoine Houasse"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "René-Antoine Houasse"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " has been named in the XVII"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "sup"
              }
            ],
            "text": "th"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " century «Iris et Morphée»."
          },
          {
            "type": "hard_break"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
